That&#39;s an array literal with one item, composed of `content`. It&#39;s the same as

```
const content : string = functionThatReturnsAString();
const arr = [];
arr.push(content);
const blob = new Blob(arr);
```

or

```
const content : string = functionThatReturnsAString();
const arr = [content];
const blob = new Blob(arr);
```

The [Blob constructor](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Blob/Blob) accepts as arguments:

    new Blob(array, options);

so the string must be put into an array first.

